---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="How these are written"
	description="Every post here carries a badge saying how AI was involved. This is what that means and how I actually write them."
	pubDate={new Date('2026-07-17')}
	aiUsage="assisted"
>
	<p>
		Every post here has a small badge at the top saying how AI was involved:
		written by hand, dictated and transcribed, AI-assisted, or written by AI.
		It's one line of frontmatter on each post, so it can't drift from the truth.
	</p>

	<p>
		Most of what I publish is AI-assisted, and I don't want that word to be
		vague. Here's what it actually means for me.
	</p>

	<p>
		I keep a voice profile. It's a plain document of how I write: the words I use
		and the ones I won't, no em-dashes, a single word in CAPS when something
		needs the weight, short sentences where they earn it and longer ones where
		they don't, a real analogy when it helps and none when it doesn't. I didn't
		invent it. I read my own posts back and wrote down what was already there.
	</p>

	<p>
		For an assisted post, the AI drafts to that profile and then I go through
		it. Most of the time that means every line: I cut the parts that sound like
		a robot, fix the rhythm, kill any word I'd never say out loud, and rewrite
		anything that isn't true to what actually happened.
	</p>

	<p>
		But I'd be lying if I said every post gets that pass. Some I work over hard.
		Some I let the AI take the wheel, read once, and ship. The care varies, and
		I'm not going to pretend it doesn't. That's the whole reason the badge
		exists: so I don't have to round up.
	</p>

	<p>
		Written by hand means I typed every word myself. AI-assisted means I
		directed the piece and edited it, but AI helped draft. Written by AI means I
		let it drive and did a lighter pass. The badge is my honest read on how much
		of me is actually in it.
	</p>

	<p>The robot helps. Sometimes it drives. The badge tells you which, and that part is always true.</p>
</Layout>
